<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 3:52PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Union
County through 415 PM EDT...
At 351 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles east of Uptown Charlotte, or 4 miles east of Mint Hill, moving
east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Fairview and New Salem.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
